When I first moved to this section of The Bronx I saw this pizza parlor and and decided to try it out. The first few times I ordered from Tony's the pizza was okay, the service was so so, and the delivery time was about 15 minutes longer then they had originally said when I called. Eventually the service and the pizza got so bad that I refuse to eat there ever again. The last time I did the pizza was SO greasy and undercooked that I couldn't even eat it and the sausage calzone that I had ordered made me sick for 2 days!!! Very disappointing. If you live in this area and have had the same consistant disappointment that I've had with Tony's Pizzeria on 233rd and White Plains Road then I HIGHLY recommend calling Angelo's Pizzeria on McLean Ave. They run a FRIENDLY business, fast delivery, good service, and the pizza is great!!!
